5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING THE TAXATION OF COAL AND
6 ELECTRICAL ENERGY PRODUCED IN THE STATE; CREATING THE STATE ENERGY RESOURCE
7 SEVERANCE ACT; PROVIDING FOR A TAX ON ELECTRICAL ENERGY PRODUCTION; PROVIDING AN
8 EXEMPTION FROM THE ELECTRICAL ENERGY PRODUCTION TAX FOR COAL; PROVIDING THE
9 ELECTRICAL ENERGY PRODUCTION TAX IS BASED ON SALE PRICE BY THE ELECTRICAL ENERGY
10 PRODUCER; REDUCING THE TAX RATE OF THE COAL SEVERANCE TAX TO MATCH THE ELECTRICAL
11 ENERGY PRODUCTION TAX RATE; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; PROVIDING FOR ADMINISTRATION AND
12 ENFORCEMENT OF THE ELECTRICAL ENERGY PRODUCTION TAX BY THE DEPARTMENT OF
13 REVENUE; CREATING STATE SPECIAL REVENUE ACCOUNTS FOR DISTRIBUTION OF ELECTRICAL
14 ENERGY TAX REVENUE; ALLOCATING REVENUE TO A TRUST ACCOUNT; PROVIDING THAT REVENUE
15 FROM THE TRUST ACCOUNT AND THE ELECTRICAL ENERGY PRODUCTION TAX MUST BE USED FOR
16 LOCAL GOVERNMENT INFRASTRUCTURE PROJECTS TRADITIONALLY FUNDED BY COAL; PROVIDING
17 CONTINGENT FUNDING FOR A STATE ENERGY AUTHORITY; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY;
18 AMENDING SECTION 15-35-103, MCA; AND PROVIDING EFFECTIVE DATES, AN APPLICABILITY DATE,
19 AND A CONTINGENT TERMINATION DATE.”
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Short title. [Sections 1 through 16] may be cited as the "State Energy
24 Resource Severance Act".
25
26 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 16], unless the context
27 clearly indicates otherwise, the following definitions apply:
28 (1) "Electrical energy producer" means each person or other organization engaged in the
