2 wind, solar, or any other means, for barter, sale, or exchange.
3 (2) "Sale price" means the gross sale price without any deduction measured at the place of
4 production.
5
6 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Rate of tax -- exemption. (1) Except as provided in subsection (2), an
7 energy severance tax is imposed for the use of the state's resources to produce electricity. The tax is imposed
8 at a rate of 10% 2% of the sale price of electricity by an electrical energy producer.
9 (2) The following electrical generation is exempt from the provisions of [sections 1 through 16]:
10 (a) electrical generation from coal or coal-fired steam turbines; and
11 (b) electrical generation facilities used for noncommercial purposes or exclusively for agricultural
12 purposes.
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Returns -- payment -- authority of department -- rulemaking. (1) On
15 or before the 30th day of the month following the end of the calendar quarter in which the tax imposed by
16 [sections 1 through 16] is payable, a return, on a form provided by the department, and payment of the tax for
17 the preceding calendar quarter must be filed with the department.
18 (2) Each electrical energy producer in this state that is subject to the tax under [sections 1 through
19 16] shall file a return.
20 (3) (a) A person required to collect and pay to the department the tax imposed by [sections 1
21 through 16] shall keep records, render statements, make returns, and comply with the provisions of [sections 1
22 through 16] and the rules prescribed by the department. Each return or statement must include the information
23 required by the rules of the department.
24 (b) For the purpose of determining compliance with the provisions of [sections 1 through 16], the
25 department is authorized to examine or cause to be examined any books, papers, records, or memoranda
26 relevant to making a determination of the amount of tax due, whether the books, papers, records, or
27 memoranda are the property of or in the possession of the person filing the return or another person. In
28 determining compliance, the department may use statistical sampling and other sampling techniques consistent
- 2 - Authorized Print Version – HB 326

