11 NEW SECTION. Section 13. State energy resources trust account for state projects. (1) There is
12 state energy resources trust account within the permanent fund type. There must be deposited in the fund
13 money received from an electrical energy producer that is allocated to the fund pursuant to [sections 1 through
14 16].
15 (2) The state treasurer shall transfer on a quarterly basis the amount of earnings, excluding
16 unrealized gains and losses, to the regional special revenue account to meet the obligations of the state that
17 are payable from the account in accordance with 90-6-710.
18 (3) The principal in the trust fund must be retained and may not be appropriated unless the
19 balance exceeds $250 million.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 14. Collection of tax -- disposition of revenue. (1) An electrical energy
22 producer shall remit the tax imposed under [section 3] to the department pursuant to the provisions of [sections
23 1 through 16].
24 (2) The tax collected under [sections 1 through 16] must, in accordance with the provisions of 17-
25 2-124, be deposited as follows:
26 (a) 50% in the state energy resources trust account for state projects established in [section 13];
27 (b) 40% in the Montana energy authority operations account established in [section 15]; and
28 (c) 10% in the Montana energy authority resource trust account established in [section 16].
